<li id="cite_note-68"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68" title="">^</a></b> The aforementioned Islamic <a href="/wiki/Satanic_Verses#Complete_Account_.28Tabar.C4.AB.29" title="Satanic Verses">histories recount</a> that as Muhammad was reciting Sūra Al-Najm (Q.53), as revealed to him by the <a href="/wiki/Angel_Gabriel" title="Angel Gabriel">angel Gabriel</a>, Satan tempted him to utter the following lines after verses 19 and 20: "Have you thought of Allāt and al-'Uzzā and Manāt the third, the other; These are the exalted Gharaniq, whose intercession is hoped for." (Allāt, al-'Uzzā and Manāt were three goddesses worshiped by the Meccans). cf Ibn Ishaq, A. Guillaume p. 166.</li>
